headlines.description: — Paolo Banchero scored 32 points, Franz Wagner had 26 points and the Orlando used a late run for a 111-104 win over the Charlotte Hornets on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Paolo Banchero scores 32 points to lead Magic to 111-104 win over Hornets

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Detroit Pistons

headlines.description: — Marcus Sasser scored a career-high 27 points in 26 minutes off the bench and the Detroit Pistons routed the San Antonio Spurs 122-96 on Tuesday night for their second consecutive victory without injured star Cade Cunningham.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pistons win again without Cunningham, beat Spurs 122-96 behind Sasser's big game off bench

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Miami Heat

headlines.description: — Bam Adebayo scored 27 points, Tyler Herro scored 20 and the Miami Heat spoiled Jimmy Butler’s return game with a one-sided 112-86 win over the Golden State Warriors on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Heat roll past Warriors in Butler's return game, winning 112-86

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Karl-Anthony Towns had 26 points, 12 rebounds and 11 assists for his first triple-double in more than three years, helping the New York Knicks defeat the Dallas Mavericks 128-113 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Karl-Anthony Towns' first triple-double in 3 years lifts Knicks over Mavericks 128-113

headlines.description: — Jalen Green scored 32 points ahd had 11 rebounds and the Houston Rockets beat the Atlanta Hawks 121-114 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jalen Green scores 32 points and has 11 rebounds as Rockets beat Hawks 121-114

headlines.description: — Desmond Bane scored 21 points, Jaren Jackson had 19 and the Memphis Grizzlies, playing without Ja Morant, used a dominant second half for a 140-103 win over the Utah Jazz on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bane scores 21 and Grizzlies use dominant second half to dispatch Jazz, 140-103

events.name: Cleveland Cavaliers at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Darius Garland had 27 points and eight assists to lead the Cleveland Cavaliers to a 122-111 win over the Portland Trail Blazers on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Darius Garland scores 27 points to lead Cavaliers over Trail Blazers 122-111

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Sacramento Kings

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 32 points to lead the Oklahoma City Thunder to their seventh straight win and 60th of the season with a 121-105 victory over the Sacramento Kings on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thunder beat the Kings 121-105 for their 7th straight win
